<h3 id="dataday-mexico-mexico-city-2020">DataDay Mexico, Mexico City 2020</h3>

<p><a href="https://sg.com.mx/datadays/">DataDays Mexico</a> is a data conference that tries to adopt a healthy dose of scepticism into the discussion of data science projects and products, and encourages speakers to also speak about things that did not always work as well as they wished for. My presentation was a reflection on my MSc dissertation project, and the big lessons it taught me in terms of using the tools of data science in a domain where I have limited expertise. Itâ€™s called: <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/raphaelleroffo/raphaelleroffo.github.io/main/docs/assets/pdf/DataDay%20Mexico%202020-08-06.pdf">â€œLessons learned working with real-life data in resource constrained settings, with limited domain knowledgeâ€</a>.</p>

